@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
    <h1>Your reading history should stay under your control.</h1>
    <p>
        This prototype highlights private shelf support, controlled profile visibility, and reader-centered organization.
        In a production build, user data would be protected with authentication, authorization, and secure storage.
    </p>
</section>

<div class="info-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h3>Private shelves</h3>
        <p>Users can keep selected reading lists hidden while still using the same tracking workflow.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="info-card">
        <h3>Profile control</h3>
        <p>Readers decide what activity becomes social and what stays personal.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="info-card">
        <h3>Future security</h3>
        <p>Authentication, secure sessions, and validated input would be the next steps for a full release.</p>
    </article>
</div>
